Here’s an example configuration snippet from `claude_desktop_config.json` for connecting a Docker MCP server:


"mcpServers": {
  "MCP_DOCKER": {
    "command": "docker",
    "args": [
      "mcp",
      "gateway",
      "run",
      "--name", "mcp-gateway",
      "--publish", "3000:3000",
      "docker/mcp-gateway:latest"
    ]
  }
}


This configuration tells Claude Desktop to run the MCP gateway as a Docker container, exposing it on port 3000. The server dynamically exposes all enabled MCP tools to Claude.
